        "D. Failure to perform periodic inventory counts of merchandise"
      ],
      "correct": 1,
      "justification_correct": "Per CFE Manual 2024, lapping requires continuous access to both incoming payments and customer account records to perpetually shift stolen funds across accounts. Segregation of duties between receipts and A/R reconciliation is the primary detective control. Without separation, perpetrators can indefinitely manipulate aging reports and conceal shortfalls through inter-account transfers.",
      "justification_wrong": "While mandatory vacations (B) aid detection, the fundamental deficiency enabling lapping is combined access to cash and records. Physical security (C) addresses theft opportunities but not concealment mechanisms. Inventory counts (D) are irrelevant to cash receipts fraud schemes per Financial Transactions chapter standards.",
      "difficulty": "STANDARD",
      "legacy": true,
      "legacy_source": "financial_transactions/quiz_001_en.json"
    },
